de.bpmnaftool.model.aristaflow
Interface AristaFlowModel

All Known Implementing Classes:
AristaFlowModelImpl
public interface AristaFlowModel

Representation of an AristaFlow model. It constructs, stores and retrieves all model elements.

Author:
Felix Härer

setNodeIds

void setNodeIds(Node node,
                Node splitNode,
                int branchId)
Sets the IDs of the given node. IDs are topoId, branchId, SplitNode and CorrespondingBlockNode. TopoId is incremented and does not need to be passed to this method, CorrespondingBlockNode is set to the start node. CorrespondingBlockNode and SplitNode are not set for StartNode or EndNode.

Parameters:
node - Node where ID's need to be set
splitNode - Last AndNode or XorNode, @see AristaFlowModel
branchId - ID of the branch, @see AristaFlowModel

setNodeIds

void setNodeIds(Node node,
                Node splitNode)
Sets the IDs of the given node. IDs are topoId, branchId, SplitNode and CorrespondingBlockNode. TopoId is incremented and does not need to be passed to this method, CorrespondingBlockNode is set to the start node. CorrespondingBlockNode and SplitNode are not set for StartNode or EndNode. BranchId is incremented automatically.

Parameters:
node - Node where ID's need to be set
splitNode - Last AndNode or XorNode, @see AristaFlowModel
